ing John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":41,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Knight Thomas de Worthington was born in 1183, in Worthington, Lancashire, England, his father, Knight Robert de Worthington, was 33 and his mother, Alice de Charnock, was 32. He married Alice of England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He lived in Worthington, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom in 1212. He died in 1242, in Worthington, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 59."},"et":{"1183–1242":"1183–1242","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1220–1282":"1220–1282","1222–Male":"1222–Surnud","1150–1213":"1150–1213","1152–1202":"1152–1202","before 1213":"enne 1213","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1152":"1152","1183":"1183","1150":"1150","1282":"1282","1215":"1215","1202":"1202","1224":"1224","1213":"1213","1212":"1212","1222":"1222","Worthington, Lancashire, England":"Worthington, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Worthington and Coppull":"Worthington, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Worthington Manor, Worthington, Lancashire, England":"Worthington, Lancashire, England","Lancashire,England":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1183–1242":"1183–1242","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1220–1282":"1220–1282","1222–Male":"1222–Kuollut","1150–1213":"1150–1213","1152–1202":"1152–1202","before 1213":"ennen vuotta 1213","1220":"1220","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1152":"1152","1183":"1183","1150":"1150","1282":"1282","1215":"1215","1202":"1202","1224":"1224","1213":"1213"